{
  "number": 2743,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2743",
  "title": "feat: add GeoSearch widget & connector",
  "body": "This PR adds a GeoSearch connector and a widget implemented with Google Maps.\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2018-03-02 at 08 57 46](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6513513/36888905-d2fa487c-1df7-11e8-8e8b-d972cce49b35.png)\r\n\r\n**Support**:\r\n- refine on interaction\r\n- control the interaction from the widget\r\n- work out of the box with Places (aka with a GeoCoding widget)\r\n- built-in / HTML marker\r\n- URLSync\r\n\r\n**Don't support**:\r\n- InfoWindow / InfoBox out of the box, can be plug (see the examples)\r\n- Widget communication out of the box, can be plug (see the examples)\r\n\r\n**Known issue**:\r\n- the docs is far from perfect, don't hesitate to give feedbacks!\r\n- doesn't work with an array for the `_geoloc` attribute, only works with an object\r\n- only work with hits for now (don't work with facets values for example), but we can probably find a solution for that with the connector implementation\r\n\r\n**Will change**:\r\n- ~~design & markup: will review the UX/design with the design team. After the design review we should directly integrate the GeoSearch markup in IS.css~~\r\n\r\nYou can play with the example on [DevNovel](https://deploy-preview-2743--algolia-instantsearch.netlify.com/v2/dev-novel/?selectedStory=GeoSearch.default). Look at the code source of the examples, especially for the InfoWindow, InfoBox & Hits communication. Don't hesitate to give some feedbacks on the behaviour or report bugs!\r\n",
